    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER AND AUXILIARY GAUGE SWITCH PACK - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        FUEL FILTER WARNING LAMP
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x08254093" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="4">
        <title>FUEL FILTER WARNING LAMP</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f0825408" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0825413.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Fuel Filter Warning Lamp Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. VACUUM SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRIVE TRAIN 1939 DATA LINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER (EGC)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825408">fuel filter warning lamp</hotlnk>
                should light during the EGC gauge sweep, after the key is turned to the ignition position. If the lamp
                doesn't light during the gauge sweep the lamp could be burned out or there may be a problem in the EGC.
            </para>
            <para>The fuel filter warning lamp lights when there is a restriction in the fuel filter system. A vacuum
                switch in the fuel filter provides a ground to the ESC which will generate the signal to activate the
                lamp. The light should go out when the fuel restriction is removed.
            </para>
            <para>The most probable cause of a warning lamp malfunction, other than a burned out lamp, is a problem with
                the vacuum sensor.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Diagnostics</title>
            <para>The electronic service tool (EZ-Tech) running the "INTUNE" diagnostic software can be used to check
                operation of the light and monitor activation of the fuel filter vacuum switch.
            </para>
